<a href="/wiki/Logudorese_dialect" title="Logudorese dialect">Logudorese Sardinian</a>, <i>nuraxis</i> in <a href="/wiki/Campidanese_dialect" title="Campidanese dialect">Campidanese Sardinian</a>, plurals of <i><a href="/wiki/Nuraghe" title="Nuraghe">nuraghe</a></i> and <i>nuraxi</i> respectively.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-21"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sardiniapoint.it/5085.html">"SP INTERVISTA&gt;GIOVANNI UGAS: SHARDANA"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASardinia&amp;rft.btitle=SP+INTERVISTA%3EGIOVANNI+UGAS%3A+SHARDANA&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sardiniapoint.it%2F5085.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-22"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Claudian, De Bello Gildonico, IV A.D.: city located in front of Libya (Africa), founded by the powerful Tyro, Karalis extends in length, between the waves, with a small bumpy hill, disperses headwinds. It follows a port in the mid of the sea, and all strong winds are softened in the shelter of the pond.(521.Urbs Lybiam contra Tyrio fundata potenti 521. Tenditur in longum Caralis, tenuemque per undas 522. Obvia dimittit fracturum flamina collem. 523. Efficitur portus medium mare: tutaque ventis 524. Omnibus, ingenti mansuescunt stagna recessu)</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEBrigaglia.2C_Mastino.2C_Ortu200627-23"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBrigaglia.2C_Mastino.2C_Ortu200627_23-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBrigaglia.2C_Mastino.2C_Ortu200627_23-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFBrigaglia.2C_Mastino.2C_Ortu2006">Brigaglia, Mastino, Ortu 2006</a>, p.&#160;27.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Piero Meloni, La Sardegna romana, Sassari, Chiarella, 1975, p. 4.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.unrv.com/provinces/sardinia.php">"Sardinia - Province of the Roman Empire"</a>. <i>www.unrv.com</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2017-07-18</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASardinia&amp;rft.atitle=Sardinia+-+Province+of+the+Roman+Empire&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.unrv.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrv.com%2Fprovinces%2Fsardinia.php&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTECasula1994133-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTECasula1994133_26-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFCasula1994">Casula 1994</a>, p.&#160;133.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Vandals by Andy Merrills and Richard Miles, published by John Wiley &amp; Sons, 2010, p. 136. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=yTIHPoyMOFYC&amp;lpg=PA136&amp;ots=uWPO55GMI4&amp;dq=Vandal%20rule%20in%20sardinia&amp;pg=PA136#v=onepage&amp;q=Vandal%20rule%20in%20sardinia&amp;f=false">[1]</a> Retrieved 12 October 2010</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.provinciadelsole.it/eng/bizantina.html">"Provicia del Sole \xe2\x80\x93 Siena"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASardinia&amp;rft.btitle=Provicia+del+Sole+%E2%80%93+Siena&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.provinciadelsole.it%2Feng%2Fbizantina.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTECasula1994137-138-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTECasula1994137-138_29-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFCasula1994">Casula 1994</a>, p.&#160;137-138.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Italia, Stephan H\xc3\xbctzen &amp; MT Publisher. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sardegna.net/docs/cultura/storia_en.html">"Sardinia - History of Sardinia"</a>. <i>www.sardegna.net</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2017-07-18</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASardinia&amp;rft.atitle=Sardinia+-+History+of+Sardinia&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephan+H%C3%BCtzen+%26+MT+Publisher&amp;rft.aulast=Italia&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.sardegna.net&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sardegna.net%2Fdocs%2Fcultura%2Fstoria_en.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Wolf Heinz J., 1998, Toponomastica barbaricina. Microtoponomastica dei comuni di Fonni, Gavoi, Lodine, Mamoiada, Oliena, Ollolai, Olzai, Org\xc3\xb3solo, Ovodda, Insula Edizioni</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Gregorius I, Epistolae, Liber Quartus, Epistola XXIII: \xe2\x80\x9cAd Hospitonem ducem barbaricinorum: Gregorius Hospitoni duci Barbaricinorum. Cum de gente vestra nemo Christianus sit, in hoc scio quia omni gente tua es melior, quia tu in ea Christianus inveniris. Dum enim Barbaricini omnes, ut insensata animalia vivant, Deum verum nesciant, ligna autem et lapides adorent, in eo ipso quod Deum verum colis, quantum omnes antecedas ostendis. Sed fidem quam percepisti etiam bonis actibus exsequere et verbis, et Christo, cui credis, offer quod praevales, ut ad eum quoscunque potueris adducas, eosque baptizari facias, et aeternam vitam diligere admoneas. Quod si fortasse ipse agere non potes, quia ad aliud occuparis, salutans peto ut hominibus (0692C) nostris, quos illuc transmisimus, fratri scilicet et coepiscopo meo Felici, filioque meo Cyriaco servo Dei, solatiari in omnibus debeas, ut dum eorum labores adiuvas, devotionem tuam omnipotenti Domino ostendas; et ipse tibi in bonis actibus adiutor sit, cuius tu in bono opere famulis solatiaris. Benedictionem vero sancti Petri apostoli per eos vobis transmisimus, quam peto ut debeatis benigne suscipere. Mense Iunio, indictione 12\xe2\x80\x9d</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Sardes-33"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Sardes_33-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Edwardes, Charles (1889). <i>Sardinia and the Sardes</i>. London: R. Bentley and Son. p.&#160;249.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASardinia&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles&amp;rft.aulast=Edwardes&amp;rft.btitle=Sardinia+and+the+Sardes&amp;rft.date=1889&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=249&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=R.+Bentley+and+Son&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-P._Grierson_1998.2C_p._287-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-P._Grierson_1998.2C_p._287_34-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-P._Grierson_1998.2C_p._287_34-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">P. Grierson &amp; L.Travaini, Medieval European Coinage, Cambridge University Press, 1998, p. 287.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-35"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Cosentino, Salvatore (2004). <i>Byzantine Sardinia between East and West</i>. Berlin, New York: Millennium. pp.&#160;329\xe2\x80\x93367.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASardinia&amp;rft.aufirst=Salvatore&amp;rft.aulast=Cosentino&amp;rft.btitle=Byzantine+Sardinia+between+East+and+West&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=329-367&amp;rft.place=Berlin%2C+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Millennium&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTECasula1994163-36"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTECasula1994163_36-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFCasula1994">Casula 1994</a>, p.&#160;163.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-37"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">\xce\x9a\xcf\x8d\xcf\x81\xce\xb9\xce\xb5 \xce\xb2\xce\xbf\xce\xae\xce\xb8\xce\xb5 \xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xe1\xbf\xa6 \xce\xb4\xce\xbf\xe1\xbf\xa6\xce\xbb\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xcf\x83\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 T\xce\xbf\xcf\x85\xcf\x81\xce\xba\xce\xbf\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x85\xcf\x81\xce\xaf\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xe1\xbc\x85\xcf\x81\xcf\x87\xcf\x89\xce\xbd\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x82 \xce\xa3\xce\xb1\xcf\x81\xce\xb4\xce\xb9\xce\xbd\xce\xaf\xce\xb1\xcf\x82 \xce\xba\xce\xb1\xce\xaf \xcf\x84\xce\xae\xcf\x82 \xce\xb4\xce\xbf\xcf\x8d\xce\xbb\xce\xb7\xcf\x82 \xcf\x83\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xce\x93\xce\xb5\xcf\x84\xce\xb9\xcf\x84 2) T\xce\xbf\xcf\x85\xcf\x81\xce\xba\xce\xbf\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x85\xcf\x81\xce\xaf\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xce\xb2\xce\xb1\xcf\x83\xce\xb9\xce\xbb\xce\xb9\xce\xba\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xcf\x89\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x83\xcf\x80\xce\xb1\xce\xb8\xce\xb1\xcf\x81\xce\xaf\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xce\xba\xce\xb1\xce\xb9 \xce\xa3\xce\xb1\xce\xbb\xce\xbf\xcf\x85\xcf\x83\xce\xaf\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xcf\x84\xcf\x89\xce\xbd \xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xce\xb3\xce\xb5\xce\xbd\xce\xb5\xcf\x83\xcf\x84\xce\xac\xcf\x84\xcf\x89\xce\xbd \xce\xb1\xcf\x81\xcf\x87\xcf\x8c\xce\xbd\xcf\x84\xcf\x89\xce\xbd.) R. CORONEO, Scultura mediobizantina in Sardegna, Nuoro, Poliedro, 2000</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-38"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Antiquitas nostra primum Calarense iudicatum, quod tunc erat caput tocius Sardinie, armis subiugavit, et regem Sardinie Musaitum nomine civitati Ianue captum adduxerunt, quem per episcopum qui tunc Ianue erat, aule sacri palatii in Alamanniam mandaverunt, intimantes regnum illius nuper esse additum ditioni Romani imperii." \xe2\x80\x93 Oberti Cancellarii, Annales p 71, Georg Heinrich (a cura di) MGH, Scriptores, Hannoverae, 1863, XVIII, pp. 56\xe2\x80\x9396</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cr\xc3\xb3nica del califa \xe2\x80\x98Abd ar-Rahm\xc3\xa2n III an-N\xc3\xa2sir entre los a\xc3\xb1os 912\xe2\x80\x93942,(al-Muqtabis V), \xc3\xa9dicion. a cura de P. CHALMETA \xe2\x80\x93 F. CORRIENTE, Madrid,1979, p. 365 Tuesday, 24 August 942 (A.D.), a messenger of the Lord of the island of Sardinia appeared at the gate of al-Nasir (...) asking for a treaty of peace and friendship. With him were the merchants, people Malfat, known in al-Andalus as from Amalfi, with the whole range of their precious goods, ingots of pure silver, brocades etc. ... transactions which drew gain and great benefits</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-40"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-40">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">To the Archont of Sardinia: a bulla with two gold bisolida with this written: from the very Christian Lord to the Archont of Sardinia. (\xce\xb5\xe1\xbd\xb6\xcf\x82 \xcf\x84\xe1\xbd\xb8\xce\xbd \xe1\xbc\x84\xcf\x81\xcf\x87\xce\xbf\xce\xbd\xcf\x84\xce\xb1 \xce\xa3\xce\xb1\xcf\x81\xce\xb4\xce\xb1\xce\xbd\xce\xaf\xce\xb1\xcf\x82. \xce\xb2\xce\xbf\xcf\x8d\xce\xbb\xce\xbb\xce\xb1 \xce\xba\xcf\x81\xcf\x85\xcf\x83\xe1\xbf\x86 \xce\xb4\xce\xb9\xcf\x83\xce\xbf\xce\xbb\xce\xb4\xce\xaf\xce\xb1. "\xce\xba\xce\xad\xce\xbb\xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xcf\x83\xce\xb9\xcf\x82 \xe1\xbd\xb2\xce\xba \xcf\x84\xe1\xbf\xb6\xce\xbd \xcf\x86\xce\xb9\xce\xbb\xce\xbf\xcf\x87\xcf\x81\xce\xaf\xcf\x83\xcf\x84\xcf\x89\xce\xbd \xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xcf\x83\xcf\x80\xce\xbf\xcf\x84\xe1\xbf\xb6\xce\xbd \xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xe1\xbd\xb8\xcf\x82 \xcf\x84\xe1\xbd\xb8\xce\xbd \xe1\xbc\x84\xcf\x81\xcf\x87\xce\xbf\xce\xbd\xcf\x84\xce\xb1 \xce\xa3\xce\xb1\xcf\x81\xce\xb4\xce\xb1\xce\xbd\xce\xaf\xce\xb1\xcf\x82.") Reiske, Johann Jakob: Leich, Johannes Heinrich, eds. (1829). Constantini Porphyrogeniti Imperatoris De Ceremoniis Aulae Byzantinae libri duo graece et latini e recensione Io. Iac. Reiskii cum eiusdem commentariis integris. Corpus Scriptorum Historiae Byzantinae 1 (Leipzig (1751\xe2\x80\x9354) ed.). Bonn: Weber. pag. 690</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-41"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-41">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">F. CODERA, Moch\xc3\xa9id, conquistador de Cerde\xc3\xb1a, in Centenario della nascita di Michele Amari. Scritti di filologia e storia araba; geografia, storia, diritto della Sicilia medioevale; studi bizantini e giudaici relativi all\xe2\x80\x99Italia meridionale nel medio evo; documenti sulle relazioni fra gli Stati italiani e il Levante, vol. II, Palermo 1910, pp. 115\xe2\x80\x9333, p. 124</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-42"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-42">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">B. MARAGONIS, Annales pisani a.1004\xe2\x80\x931175, ed. K. PERTZ, in MGH, Scriptores, 19, Hannoverae, 1861/1963, pp. 236\xe2\x80\x932 and Gli Annales Pisani di Bernardo Maragone, a cura di M. L.GENTILE, in Rerum Italicarum Scriptores, n.e., VI/2, Bologna 1930, pp. 4\xe2\x80\x937. 1017. Fuit Mugietus reversus in Sardineam, et cepit civitatem edificare ibi atque homines Sardos vivos in cruce murare. Et tunc Pisani et Ianuenses illuc venere, et ille propter pavorem eorum fugit in Africam. Pisani vero et Ianuenses reversi sunt Turrim, in quo insurrexerunt Ianuenses in Pisanos, et Pisani vicerunt illos et eiecerunt eos de Sardinea</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-43"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-43">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Almanacco scolastico della Sardegna, p. 101</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-44"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Birocchi, I.; Mattone, A. (2004). <i>La carta de logu d\'Arborea nella storia del diritto medievale e moderno</i>. Laterza.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASardinia&amp;rft.au=Mattone%2C+A.&amp;rft.aufirst=I.&amp;rft.aulast=Birocchi&amp;rft.btitle=La+carta+de+logu+d%27Arborea+nella+storia+del+diritto+medievale+e+moderno&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pub=Laterza&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTECasula1994209-210-212-45"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTECasula1994209-210-212_45-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFCasula1994">Casula 1994</a>, p.&#160;209-210-212.</span></li>\n<li 